  "text": "The four major kubelet components owned by sig-node are implemented across these key files in kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0:\n\n1. **Pod Lifecycle Manager**: Implemented in pkg/kubelet/pod_workers.go and pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go. The PodWorkers interface (pkg/kubelet/pod_workers.go) manages the lifecycle of pods through its UpdatePod() method, handling three states: SyncPod (creation/running), TerminatingPod (shutdown), and TerminatedPod (cleanup). The main orchestration happens in pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go where the SyncPod() method (lines 1795-1840) implements the transaction script for pod synchronization. It calls the container runtime's SyncPod callback after handling volumes, secrets, and other pod preparation.\n\n2. **Container Runtime Interface (CRI) Client**: Implemented in pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/kuberuntime_manager.go. The kubeGenericRuntimeManager struct (lines 98-150+) implements the CRI client and contains the gRPC service clients (runtimeService and imageService). The SyncPod method (lines 1119-1160+) orchestrates container lifecycle through 8 steps: computing pod actions, killing old sandboxes, killing unwanted containers, creating sandboxes, creating containers, resizing containers, and updating configurations. It interfaces with the CRI through the internalapi.RuntimeService and internalapi.ImageManagerService interfaces.\n\n3. **Volume Manager**: Implemented in pkg/kubelet/volumemanager/volume_manager.go. The VolumeManager interface (lines 93-150+) provides methods for managing volume lifecycle including WaitForAttachAndMount(), WaitForUnmount(), and GetMountedVolumesForPod(). It runs asynchronous loops (the reconciler and populator) to attach, mount, unmount, and detach volumes based on the actual and desired state of the world caches.\n\n4. **Device Plugin Manager**: Implemented in pkg/kubelet/pluginmanager/plugin_manager.go. The PluginManager interface (lines 35-44) manages plugin registration/deregistration through the Run() method and plugin handler management via AddHandler(). The pluginManager struct (lines 83-104) coordinates between the plugin watcher (desiredStateOfWorldPopulator), reconciler, and caches to manage device plugins and other kubelet plugins.\n\nAll components are confirmed to be owned by sig-node through the OWNERS file (pkg/kubelet/OWNERS), which lists sig-node-approvers and sig-node-reviewers as the maintainers. These components work together to provide pod lifecycle management, container runtime communication, volume handling, and device plugin support to the kubelet."
